abstract: VINELAND, N.J., Sept. 2. -- "Johnny" Hughes, the counterfeiter, is dying of cancer of the liver. McGee, who was head of the anthropological department of the World's Fair, was in St. Louis to-day on his way back to Washington after a remarkable four months' experiment in the Great American Desert, Arizona. abstract: WASHINGTON, Sept. 7. -- In the United States 100,000,000 pounds of prunes are eaten yearly. abstract: NEWPORT, Sept. 20. -- On the heels of the organization of the Municipal Reform League by the men came the organization to-day of the Civic League of Newport by the women. The objects are to promote, by education and co-operation, a higher public opinion and a better social order, to keep constantly before the public suggestions for better municipal and social conditions, and to create a widespread interest in the development of the city.

abstract: The possession of a deep voice, having also a penetrating quality, was the famous asset of a Stock Exchange operator years ago. When he was on a bear crusade he would stand in a crowd where prices were falling and groan: "N-o b-ot- t-o-m! N-o b-o-t-t-o-m!" abstract: BERLIN, Sept. 23. -- Several distressing instances of children's suicides have occurred since the Autumn school term began. abstract: QUEEN ZIXI OF IX," the new juvenile by L. Frank Baum, which the Century Company is issuing this week, is an old-fashioned fairy story. Among the "extravagancies" in it are a magic cloak which grants a wish to every wearer, an old statue which makes a peasant boy King of Noland, a race of queer, mischievous monsters called "Roly-Rogues," and fairies and a beautiful witch-queen.

abstract: WASHINGTON, Sept. 29. -- Washington's poor fielding gave St. Louis to-day's game. In the fourth inning a base on balls and three singles, with the assistance of four errors, enabled the visitors to gain a lead which the home team could not overcome. Morgan of St. Louis was put off the field for criticising the umpire's decisions.
